title:Maple Sugar Biscuits
ingredients:2 cups flour//
1/2 teaspoon salt//
4 teaspoons baking powder//
4 Tablespoons shortening//
3/4 cup milk//
1 cup maple sugar
instructions:sift each dry ingredient into a bowl.//
Mix in the shortening.//
Add milk to make a soft dough.//
Pat or roll out to make 1/2 inch thick.//
Cut with small biscuit cutter.//
Spread with softened butter, grated maple sugar, and cinnamon if desired.//
Bake in greased pan or baking sheet at 400F for about 15 minutes.